Senate President Ahmad Lawan has reappointed three media aides who served under the immediate past Senate President Bukola Saraki. The three media aides are Mohammed Isa, special assistant on media and publicity; Olu Onemola, special assistant on new media, and Tope Brown Olowoyeye, senior legislative aide on media and publicity (photographer). Our correspondent reports that the three appointees all served in the same positions under Saraki. Lawan also appointed Mrs Betty Okoroh, special assistant on administration and Okechukwu Nwankwoh as senior legislative aide on schedules and events. The appointments were contained in a letter dated June 19, and signed by the Chief of Staff to the senate president Babagana Muhammad Aji.  Saraki as President of the 8th Senate Gov. Dankwambo’s  media aide dies Saraki’s aides submit handover notes Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin